            . I am helper in Mr. Vansittart's stable, or in the <placeName id="t18320517-261-crimeloc1496">Hay-mews</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18320517-261-crimeloc1496" type="placeName" value="Hay-mews"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18320517-261-crimeloc1496" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320517-261-off1494 t18320517-261-crimeloc1496"></join>. On the 15th of May I was in a room over the stable - I heard a noise and went down stairs, I saw the prisoner walking from the stable - I went after him, and when he saw me, he ran up the mews towards Union-street, turned to the left, and then again into Charles-street, and down Chesterfield-street; I pursued - he threw the bridle down the area of No. 8 - I pursued, and took him back; a woman picked up the bridle, and gave it me from the rails - it is my master's; I said to him, "What have you done with the bridle?" and he said, "I have not a bridle about me;" I said, "Which area have you thrown it down;" I had seen it safe twenty minutes after two o'clock, and pursued him with it about four.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320517-261-person1912">
                  JOHN 
                  FLOOD
               <interp inst="t18320517-261-person1912" type="surname" value="FLOOD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320517-261-person1912" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
