                  </persName>
             (Police-constable C 7). I was on duty in Park-lane, and received the prisoner and the bridle; he said he took it through distress, to save a family from starving, and begged me to let him go - in going through the street, he begged me not to expose him publicly; I took him through some back streets, and he ran off - he beckoned the people to make way for him, and he told them to stop me - I got very ill used.</p>
